1. run router.sh script on the router
  $ chmod +x router.sh
  $ ./router.sh

( 1.5. verify that NTP is running )
  $ service ntp status

2. run server_and_clients.sh on the server and clients
  $ chmod +x server_and_clients.sh
  $ ./server_and_clients.sh

3. run the test file
  $ chmod +x testing.sh
  $ ./testing.sh

.. done

reference webite:
https://vitux.com/how-to-install-ntp-server-and-client-on-ubuntu/
